<subSubSection pageNumber="735" type="discussion">
<paragraph pageNumber="735">
<emphasis italics="true" pageNumber="735">Note:</emphasis>
A name at species rank for 
<taxonomicName class="Magnoliopsida" family="Molluginaceae" genus="Mollugo" kingdom="Plantae" order="Caryophyllales" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="verticillata">
<emphasis italics="true" pageNumber="735">Mollugo verticillata</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
var. Î² L. (1753) and not, as suggested by Jeffrey (in Hubbard &amp; Milne-Redhead, 
<emphasis italics="true" pageNumber="735">
Fl. Trop. E. Africa, 
<taxonomicName class="Magnoliopsida" family="Aizoaceae" kingdom="Plantae" order="Caryophyllales" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="family">Aizoaceae</taxonomicName>
</emphasis>
: 15. 1961), first published in 1771 where it could appear to be a superfluous name for 
<taxonomicName authority="L. (1759)" authorityName="Linnaeus" authorityYear="1759" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Molluginaceae" genus="Mollugo" kingdom="Plantae" order="Caryophyllales" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="spergula">
<emphasis italics="true" pageNumber="735">Mollugo spergula</emphasis>
L. (1759)
</taxonomicName>
. Consequently, 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Linnaeus" authorityYear="1771" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Molluginaceae" genus="Pharnaceum" kingdom="Plantae" order="Caryophyllales" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="mollugo">
<emphasis italics="true" pageNumber="735">P. mollugo</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is not homotypic with the latter, as indicated by Jeffrey.
</paragraph>
